      <span>Researchers</span><span class="c11" style="font-weight: 700;">&nbsp;found that nerve deterioration isn&rsquo;t just &ldquo;random&rdquo; or a result of aging</span><span class="c3" style="color: #000000; font-family: 'Arial'; font-size: 11pt; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline;">. Instead, it&rsquo;s often triggered by a hidden biological process that&rsquo;s quietly damaging nerve endings&mdash;24/7.</span>
